An Atlas Centaur rocketlaunching a military communications satellite went out ofcontrol a minute after launch and was destroyed, a NASAspokesman said.    The Atlas Centaur blasted off in rainy and overcastconditions. Within seconds controllers reported it was out ofcontrol and the order to blow it up was given.    NASA spokesperson Lisa Malone said the rocket may have beenstruck by lightening.    The failure is the first for NASA since May 1986, when aDelta rocket failed. Reuter&#3;